# Creating New WordPress Blocks

## Quick Block Creation
Generate a new block without creating a new plugin:
```bash
npx @wordpress/create-block block-name --no-plugin
```

## Integration Steps
1. Move generated block to `src/blocks/block-name/`
2. Add block name to `$custom_blocks` array in main plugin file
3. Run `npm run build` to compile the new block
4. Test in WordPress admin

## Block Architecture
### Required Files
- `block.json` - Block metadata, attributes, and settings
- `index.js` - Block registration and imports
- `edit.js` - Editor component (React/JSX with TypeScript support)
- `save.js` - Frontend render function

### Optional Files  
- `editor.scss` - Editor-only styles
- `style.scss` - Frontend and editor styles
- `view.js` - Frontend interactivity

### Block.json Configuration
Key properties to configure:
```json
{
  "apiVersion": 3,
  "name": "namespace/block-name",
  "title": "Block Title",
  "category": "widgets",
  "textdomain": "wp-multi-block-example",
  "editorScript": "file:./index.js",
  "editorStyle": "file:./index.css", 
  "style": "file:./style-index.css"
}
```

## Development Best Practices
- Use consistent text domain across all blocks
- Follow WordPress coding standards
- Implement proper TypeScript types for attributes
- Use React functional components with hooks
- Apply TailwindCSS for styling consistency